    author: "Khyati Srivastava",
    slug: "the-spelling-bee-sneeze",
    category: "Comedy",
    emoji: "🔤",
    excerpt: "Leo reached the final word of the spelling bee just as the biggest sneeze of his life arrived.",
    created_at: "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z",
    body: "<p style='color:#6a4b8f;font-style:italic;margin-bottom:18px'>By Khyati Srivastava</p><p>Leo stood at the microphone, one word away from winning the district spelling bee. The word was rhythm. He knew it cold. He opened his mouth.</p><p>That was the exact moment his nose decided to betray him. A sneeze built up like a thundercloud. He fought it. He scrunched. He squinted. The judges leaned forward.</p><p>R, he began. The sneeze surged. H, he managed, voice wobbling. Y. His eyes were watering now. T. The audience held its breath. H. One letter left.</p><p>The sneeze won. AH-CHOO, he exploded, and somewhere in the spray of that mighty sneeze came a sound that might have been M.</p><p>The judges huddled. Had he said the letter, or had he just sneezed? They played it back in their minds. They argued. Finally the head judge, hiding a grin, asked Leo to simply spell the word one more time, slowly.</p><p>Leo wiped his nose, took a breath, and said it clean: R-H-Y-T-H-M. The crowd erupted.</p><p>He lifted the trophy with one hand and a tissue with the other. In his victory speech he thanked his parents, his teacher, and his nose, for keeping things exciting until the very last letter. The audience laughed so hard that two more people sneezed, which Leo declared was simply the spirit of the bee living on.</p>",
